   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER FIVE IN THE BUILDING UP</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>OF THE BODY OF CHRIST Scripture Reading: Eph 1:22-23; Rom 12:5; Eph 4:15-16; Col 2:19; Eph 4:12; 1 Cor 3:12; Eph 3:9; 1:10 OUTLINE The Body of Christ, as the church of God, being an organism like the human body Eph 1:22-23: Constituted with all the living members of Christ Rom 12:5.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Needing to grow for its building up.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>The growth of the Body of Christ: Through the members growing into the Head, Christ, in all things by holding to truth in love Eph 4:15.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Out from the Head, Christ, all the Body causes its growth Eph 4:16.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>With the growth of God Col 2:19b.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>The building up of the Body of Christ: By the Body's growth: By its members being perfected to do the work of the New Testament ministry the building up of the Body of Christ Eph 4:12.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>In the life of God Col 2:19.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>In the process of transformation 1 Cor 3:12.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>By the building up of itself: By being joined together through every joint of the rich supply Eph 4:16b.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>By being knit together through the operation in the measure of each one part Eph 4:16b.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>In love Eph 4:16c.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>The fulfillment of the eternal economy of God Eph 3:9; 1:10: By carrying out the New Testament ministry Eph 4:12.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>To complete the building up of the church for the consummation of the New Jerusalem.</S>
   </TEXT>
